    <!-- ==================== Autonomous Mode ==================== -->
    <section class="section section--border-top" id="autonomous">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="section__label">Autonomous Mode</span>
        <h2 class="section__title">
          Queue tasks. Run overnight. Wake up to working code.
        </h2>
        <p class="section__subtitle">
          Define tasks in a YAML spec file with dependencies, agent assignments,
          and timeouts. The DAG executor resolves the dependency graph and runs
          tasks in parallel phases — no supervision required.
        </p>
        <div class="autonomous-grid">
          <div class="code-block">
            <div class="code-block__header">
              <span class="code-block__dot" />
              <span class="code-block__dot" />
              <span class="code-block__dot" />
              <span class="code-block__filename">opencastle.tasks.yml</span>
            </div>
            <div class="code-block__body">
              <pre><span class="code-key">name:</span> <span class="code-string">"Overnight feature batch"</span>
<span class="code-key">concurrency:</span> 2
<span class="code-key">adapter:</span> claude-code

<span class="code-key">tasks:</span>
  - <span class="code-key">id:</span> migrate-db
    <span class="code-key">agent:</span> database-engineer
    <span class="code-key">prompt:</span> <span class="code-string">|
      Create a new migration for a reviews table.</span>
    <span class="code-key">timeout:</span> 10m

  - <span class="code-key">id:</span> build-component
    <span class="code-key">agent:</span> ui-ux-expert
    <span class="code-key">prompt:</span> <span class="code-string">|
      Build a ReviewCard component.</span>
    <span class="code-key">timeout:</span> 15m

  - <span class="code-key">id:</span> wire-page
    <span class="code-key">agent:</span> developer
    <span class="code-key">depends_on:</span> [migrate-db, build-component]
    <span class="code-key">prompt:</span> <span class="code-string">|
      Add reviews to the place detail page.</span></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="autonomous-details">
            <div class="autonomous-feature">
              <h3 class="autonomous-feature__title">DAG Execution</h3>
              <p class="autonomous-feature__desc">
                Tasks form a directed acyclic graph. The executor topologically
                sorts them into parallel phases, respecting dependencies and
                concurrency limits.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="autonomous-feature">
              <h3 class="autonomous-feature__title">Adapter Support</h3>
              <p class="autonomous-feature__desc">
                Ships with adapters for <strong>Claude Code</strong>,
                <strong>Copilot CLI</strong>, and <strong>Cursor CLI</strong>.
                Each adapter spawns the agent runtime in non-interactive
                mode with autonomous flags.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="autonomous-feature">
              <h3 class="autonomous-feature__title">Built-in Safety</h3>
              <p class="autonomous-feature__desc">
                Cycle detection prevents infinite loops. Configurable timeouts
                kill stuck tasks. Failure policies control whether to
                continue or halt the entire run.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="autonomous-feature">
              <h3 class="autonomous-feature__title">Run Reports</h3>
              <p class="autonomous-feature__desc">
                After each run, a JSON report is written with task statuses,
                durations, and output summaries. Use <code>--dry-run</code> to
                preview the execution plan first.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="autonomous-feature">
              <h3 class="autonomous-feature__title">Generate Task Spec Prompt</h3>
              <p class="autonomous-feature__desc">
                Don't write YAML by hand. Use the built-in
                <strong>Generate Task Spec</strong> prompt to describe your goal
                in plain language — the Team Lead decomposes it into a valid spec
                with dependencies, file partitions, and self-contained agent
                instructions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

